---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const pageTitle = "Privacy Policy";
const description = "Privacy Policy for AuthenticNerd.com";
const lastUpdated = "February 18, 2026";
---

<BaseLayout pageTitle={pageTitle} description={description}>
    <div class="leading-relaxed text-inherit">
    
        <section class="my-8">
            <h1 class="text-4xl italic font-bold mb-2 leading-tight text-navy dark:text-white">
                    The "Authentic Nerd" Privacy Policy
            </h1>
            <p class="text-sm opacity-70 mb-4">Last Updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
            <p class="text-lg italic border-l-4 border-terracotta pl-4 py-2 bg-navy/5 dark:bg-white/5">
                "I value your privacy as much as I value my own system's uptime."
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="my-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-navy dark:text-white">What I Track (and Why)</h2>
            <p class="mb-4">
                This site uses <strong>AWS CloudWatch RUM (Real User Monitoring)</strong>. Unlike traditional marketing 
				analytics, the goal here is System Performance, not user profiling.
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-4 ml-2">
                <li>
					<strong>Performance Metrics:</strong> I measure page load times, JavaScript errors, and Core Web 
					Vitals (LCP, CLS, INP).
				</li>
                <li>
					<strong>Anonymity:</strong> Your IP address is used only to determine your general region (e.g., 
					Newfoundland, Canada) to optimize CDN routing. Your full IP is never stored.
				</li>
                <li>
					<strong>Storage:</strong> Small, functional cookies are used by the AWS RUM client to distinguish 
					unique sessions for performance aggregation.
				</li>
                <li>
					<strong>No Cross-Site Tracking:</strong> I do not track you across other websites. There are no 
					"Like" buttons, ad pixels, or third-party marketing trackers here.
				</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="my-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-navy dark:text-white">
                Privacy Browsers & Resiliency
            </h2>
            <p class="mb-4">
                If you use a privacy-focused browser like DuckDuckGo, Brave, or extensions like uBlock Origin, my
                performance monitoring will likely be blocked.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-4">
                This is perfectly fine. My site is designed to be a <strong>Resilient System</strong>â€”it will work 
				exactly the same for you whether the monitoring script fires or not. I respect your choice to stay 
				invisible.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="my-8 border-t border-navy/10 dark:border-white/10 pt-8">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-navy dark:text-white">Contact</h2>
            <p>
                If you have questions about this policy or how your (minimal) data is handled, feel free to reach out 
				via 
                <a 
					href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jerometerry" 
					target="_blank"
					class="text-terracotta hover:underline">LinkedIn
				</a> or check the source on 
                <a 
					href="https://github.com/jerometerry/my-personal-system/tree/main/blog" 
					target="_blank"
					class="text-terracotta hover:underline">GitHub
				</a>.
            </p>
        </section>

    </div>
</BaseLayout>